Jul 15 2009	Hotel Fusion	My husband and I stayed at Hotel Fusion for one night (a stop in San Francisco on our way to Napa). We were so happy with our stay that we decided to write a review. I had researched extensively before our trip trying to find affordable hotels (but clean rooms in great locations). Hotel Fusion is this and a lot more. We paid around 75 dollars (a deal i got online through their website) and we were upgraded to a King for no reason at all. The room was beautiful, extremely clean, and pretty big. We had a flat screen t.v., built in c.d. player on wall, fridge, coffee, huge closets, and a really cute bathroom. We were right on the road, but it wasn't noisy (especially not compared to other stays and our trip to Chicago recently). Furthermore, we had a large family across the hall from us and I didn't even realize it until I saw them in the breakfast room. You could not hear anything from the other rooms at all (nice if you are a light sleeper). The Hotel has a continental breakfast that was perfect for us (bagels, toast and jam, danish, coffee, orange juice, and fresh fruit). They turned down our beds and gave us chocolate mints while we were out at night! The location of this hotel is also great. We easily walked to China Town, some of the Piers, the Financial District and more. We ate at a great Thai place down the street and had drinks at a pub around the corner. If we return to San Francisco we are definitely staying here again. I cannot say enough great things about the staff and quality of this hotel. It's not one of those hotels that's cheap but adequate (assuming you'll be out in the city anyway)...it's a hotel that is nice enough that you actually ENJOY hanging in your room - but it's really affordable!	
