Jun 9 2008 	Great little hotel!	What a little SF gem!I am a Trip Advisor fanatic, so when I was in the planning stages of a long weekend getaway in San Francisco to surprise my husband for his birthday, I spent weeks reading hotel reviews for the downtown SF area. My criteria: affordable and close to BART as we would be relying on public transportation to get around the city. I narrowed my search down to Hotel Fusion but was still a bit nervous about some of the negative reviews I had read on TA regarding thin walls, street noise, etc. and I am very sensitive to unwanted noise. We left the Hotel Fusion thrilled to death.The location of the hotel is ideal. It is one block from the BART station which was unbelievably convenient. It's also very close to the Powell Street cable car station if you're into that. A hint: the lines for the cable cars at the Powell Street station are ridiculous. If you want to ride and don't want to wait, walk up Powell Street 5 or so blocks to the next cable car stop and there is no waiting. When I contacted the hotel to book the room, I asked for a king room, and I'm pretty sure that all of these rooms are located on the top (5th) floor. The room was small, but nice and perfect for our needs. We could have spent 2 or 3 times the amount we spent on our room for a luxury room, but we really just needed a home base and didn't plan on spending much time in the room so size wasn't really an issue. For the record, I really think two double beds would have made the room feel tiny and claustrophobic but this wasn't the case with the king room. The bathroom was TINY but fine.Some of the negative reviewers have complained about the lack of A/C in the rooms which really wasn't an issue for us. During the day, we opened up the windows to get some fresh air in the room while we were out and about in the city, and the hotel provides a great little fan that helped keep the air circulating. In the evenings we closed the windows and that, combined with the fan noise, completely drowned out most street noise, aside from the random ambulance so street noise was no problem. This may have also been less of an issue for us due to being five floors above the street - who knows? But street noise didn't adversely affect our stay a bit.As for the thin walls...we really didn't experience this at all either. I don't know if we didn't have anyone next to us or not, but we didn't hear anyone in adjoining rooms at all. Not once. The front desk staff was excellent. I had requested an early check in and was told they couldn't guarantee it, but would ry. When we arrived at our hotel at 1:00, we were able to check right in, with no problem, so this definitely scored points with us.I guess if pressed, the only somewhat negative thing I could comment on was the water pressure was a little goofy at times - I showered in the room 3 times and each time the water pressure dropped down to next to nothing for a few seconds, but honestly? No big deal.We had such an amazing time and hope to make this trip an annual event. We will definitely return to Hotel Fusion.	
Jun 4 2008 	Great Hotel for the Price	I stayed at the Hotel Fusion for five days booking through Hotwire for only $69 a night. I got much more for the $69 than I expected. I found the Hotel had been newly refurbished and very modern. The rooms are small but nicely updated and all have high speed internet that worked great. They offer a &quot;mini&quot; breakfast in the morning that consists of toast or bagels and jucie and coffee. There is no air conditioning but in San Francisco that really isnt much of an issue. The rooms do get a lot of noise from the streetcars and traffic but was no more than I would expect in a busy city. The location is excellent, being in the heart of Union Square. Overall this was an excellent value in a City where rooms can easily cost three times what I paid. I would stay there again without hesitation.	
