Jan 20 2008 	great stay	Spent last 2 nights here on our San Francisco trip. My mom &amp; I walked into this hotel to check availability because we could no longer extend our stay in Stratford Hotel. The rates we got for the junior suite is a bit high because there was a Pediatrics' Convention during that time. *The junior suite #514 has a desk, cd player, a sofa bed, bedroom, 2 lcd tvs, coffee making facilities, ref, iron &amp; board. This hotel like many SanFran hotels, has no aircon facilities but they gladly provide a Honeywell fan &amp; portable cool air machine upon request. I had to use the fan because my sofa bed area has no window. Room decor is modern which I like. But the bathroom looks pale to me. Maybe because of the lighting. I saw a king deluxe room on the same floor while it was being cleaned. It was huge. Maybe I will ask for that room when I travel with my husband next time. Our room overlooks a courtyard. My mom said she slept well because it is quiet compared to Stratford LOL  The hotel smells clean. The lobby is small but the decor is modern. Reminds me a bit of home. There is free coffee, tea &amp; hot chocolate the whole day.  *The breakfast room is on the same floor as we are (5/f). But it was just a small room(507) that you get everything you need - cereal, milk, 2 kinds of juice, regular &amp; decaf coffee, 2 kinds of bread, butter &amp; jams, muffins then eat it in your room. Breakfast is included in the room rate. Adequate enough to start your day. I get mine in my pajamas at 7am. My parents wake up later so I eat alone in the desk of the room. My mom prefers to have her breakfast in Chancellor Hotel because of the eggs benedict. *Staff is friendly &amp; helpful. Celso gladly showed us the suite before we decided to take it. I forgot the other names of the other staff I dealt with during our stay. They are happy with giving me directions, always whipping out a SanFran city map. There was one morning I asked direction for Whole Foods Market store on 4th street and I said I will be taking taxi but the guy in front said it is just walking distance. He even went out of the door to point the street down after Stockton where I should head to.  I super highly recommend Whole Foods Market on 4th St.! This is the place to go if you want to eat healthy &amp; not spend too much while on your visit to SanFran. Or if you are on a certain diet like gluten-free/casein-free, vegetarian, diabetic, organic &amp; the like. I got from there fresh persimmon &amp; organic strawberries. There is also a small coffee shop on the front. They have cooked food too. I tried fried chicken &amp; garlic mashed potato to go &amp; some salad. Excellent! I think this is the nearest supermarket in the area. They called a taxi for me on my way back to the hotel with 7 bags full of stuff to bring home to Manila. Coming in late from a day trip to Napa Valley &amp; Sonoma, I asked the guy on the front desk which internet server are they connected, he said internet is free I just need to get the cable from downstairs. This is the only hotel in our US trip that offered free internet! Even if it is cable internet, I am happy. I hope next time there is wifi already. Also, they helped me find a Catholic church for a Sunday mass. Again, they pointed one that is walking distance. We did not take any packaged trip since my relatives come everyday to take us anywhere but I think the bell service up front can arrange this. My dad booked the limo that will take us to the airport at Chancellor Hotel's booth of Susan though. Because they(he&amp;mom) always do that when they are in SanFran. Creatures of habit!LOL Although I found a taxi driver willing to arrange for that too. Taxi drivers in SanFran are nice &amp; friendly people. * Location is excellent! Hotel is near Union Square but not really noisy. Subway &amp; Coldstone is across the street. Apple store on 1 Stockton St. is a short block away. I think a BART station is beside it. Everything is walking distance-accessible. There is Westfield mall nearby. H&amp;M and Gap is a few steps away. Anything you need there is a Walgreens half block away but this closes at 12 midnight. There is another Walgreens near Chancellor Hotel that is 24/7.  Shopping and window shopping is highly recommended. LV has a great staff - Kim, Angelica &amp; Robert are super! Other brands like Burberry, Tiffany, Goyard are all walking distance. There is also a big Borders bookstore - miss Vie was nice, I got a discount card and she assisted me with all my purchases and books that I need. Went there almost everyday. We had a late lunch once at Cheesecake Factory on the top floor of Macy's. Nice view of Union Square. Great service. I forgot to try Michael Mina's restaurant on Westin St.Francis though. We also had our lunch on the last day of our stay at Crustacean on California St. I love their garlic noodles. Dungeness crab is good too. Lunch for 3 is about $120. Though I think there are other restaurants that opened recently which offers the same cuisine? Will I stay here again? Yes! Either here or the Chancellor. For a longer stay, Hotel Fusion offers stay 7 nights pay for 6 I think. I hope to be back real soon! :-)	
Jan 3 2008 	Great Stay at the Fusion	I spent 6 nights at the Hotel Fusion, San Francisco and would highly recommend it. Being my first trip to San Fran, the hotel was located right in the downtown area, easy walking to shops, restaurants, bus, rail and tram services. The front desk staff were extremely helpful and friendly. We had a twin and a queen room, both were very clean, good sized and had complimentary tea/coffee making facilities. Breakfast was available in a seperate room, which was fine for us, lots of toast, muffins, mini crossiants, juice, coffee etc available.I would definately stay at the Fusion next time I visit San Fran.	
Dec 30 2007 	Excellent Hotel for the right traveller!	I read all the reviews before coming, and found them overall good, with a few exceptions I thought I could live with for $65 a night. I booked the 7 night for 5 night special and looked forward to it, cautiously. I was pleasantly suprised. Being a boutique hotel and not a bland and boring chain, it has a small but stylish lobby. Since I'venever once spent time in a hotel lobby while travelling I couldn't care less. What really blew us away was the absolutely perfect location of this hotel. When they say it is 2 blocks from the BART, streetcar and bus, they mean the two tiniest blocks in the world. The trolleys are 1 of those tiny blocks away. It is surrounded by excellent restaurants, coffee shops, and all the shopping and amenities a person could want.It neighbors very expensive hotels and is by far the easiest location for getting to Chinatown, Alcatraz, Fisherman's Wharf, the Castro, Haight, Financial District, and the Mission. There is no better location for a vacation to San Francisco! I love the Fusion and will definately stay here again.The entire hotel underwent an extensive 2 year renovation that completed just last year and it shows. There is beautiful granite everywhere, a very modern elevator with little tv's to watch while youwait (though it never took more than 2 minutes). Our room was tastefuland comfortable with a comfy bed, clean and well lit bathroom with an exhaust fan, and a flat screen TV with a DVD player built in. Our roomwas one of the smallest in the hotel, judging from views of other rooms as we saw them cleaned, and I wished for a dresser instead of a desk, but I did find the furnishings comfortable and nice and I was able to put our suitcase on one of those stands and live out of it. I wouldn't come here expecting a room the size of a football field, but I would expect it to be very nice.The hotel offered a continental breakfast of fruit, toast, coffee, croissants, muffins, milk and juice, and an exercise room we never used. Every room has a fan, ironing board, and iron, fairly affordablesnack bar (that we never used because the Walgreens drugstore was 1/2 a block away), a coffee maker, hair dryer, nice towels, shampoo, conditioner, lotion, and soap. If you are used to staying at bland chains you might find the possiblity of a smaller room in such a greaturban setting odd, otherwise, I woud recommend this hotel for your next trip to San Francisco.As a note too.. the hotel doesn't HAVE air conditioning, so the compaints about it's not working and it's noise are puzzling...check out the weather and maybe avoid the hotel if you require air conditioning in the hottest months of the year.	
